{"type":"message","id":"332b7e4e","parentId":"94e6a7ae","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:39:03.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran at 04:38:04 (newest log) after this cron triggered at 04:37:05. There's a slightly newer log `pulse_2026-03-24 043804.md` that was likely written by the pulse script execution. Let me read that one as well since it's the most recent.\n\nBut wait - this cron was triggered at 04:37, and the log shows `pulse_2026-03-24 043705.md` which matches the cron time. The pulse script then ran and created a newer log `pulse_2026-03-24 043804.md` at 04:38:04. Let me read the newest one.","thinkingSignature":"429da8fbf4b83484bf85df5147b5501cba9d3fffcaee80bfa531e00a2b135fd9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hkih8sb32laz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pwsh -Command \"Get-Content 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 043804.md' -Raw\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2087,"output":213,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14254,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774341537726}}
{"type":"message","id":"8fce6eef","parentId":"332b7e4e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:39:04.395Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hkih8sb32laz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 043804\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action identified: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the TIC experiment. Let me think about what this entails:\r\n\r\n1. Read the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md doc to understand the approach\r\n2. Create a script or method to analyze pulse logs for invariants vs variants\r\n3. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at the most recent pulse log to understand the format, and then create the TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- logs/pulse_2026-03-24 043705.md (most recent)\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC implementation that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that repeat across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Tests prediction ability\r\n\r\nLet me craft a concrete action - I'll create a TIC classifier script that starts analyzing the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight unifies Phase 1 and Phase 2 into one problem. The next concrete step is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier to test the hypothesis on actual pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and measure classification accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Compression = Causal Discovery\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"Phase \\d+\",\r\n    r\"research/\",\r\n    r\"\\.md\",\r\n    r\"^[A-Z].*COMPLETE.*$\",\r\n    r\"^\\[.*\\].*$\",  # Checklist items\r\n    r\"^##.*$\",      # Headers\r\n    r\"^###.*$\",     # Subheaders\r\n]\r\n\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # Dates\r\n    r\"\\d{6}\\.md\",          # Pulse timestamps\r\n    r\"\\d+s\",               # Durations\r\n    r\"^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2} \\d{6}$\",  # Session headers\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(pulse_file: Path) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    # Split by headers and key markers\r\n    blocks = re.split(r'\\n(?=##)', content)\r\n    return [b.strip() for b in blocks if b.strip()]\r\n\r\ndef classify_token(token: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a token as INVARIANT or VARIANT.\"\"\"\r\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, token):\r\n            return \"VARIANT\"\r\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, token):\r\n            return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    return \"UNKNOWN\"\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulse(pulse_file: Path) -> Dict[str, int]:\r\n    \"\"\"Count invariant vs variant tokens in a pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', content)\r\n    counts = {\"INVARIANT\": 0, \"VARIANT\": 0, \"UNKNOWN\": 0}\r\n    for token in tokens:\r\n        classification = classify_token(token)\r\n        counts[classification] += 1\r\n    return counts\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants: set, pulse_n: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict content of next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    # Simple baseline: repeat invariant structure\r\n    return f\"pulse_n+1 inherits {len(invariants)} invariant patterns\"\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment() -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    results = {\r\n        \"total_pulses\": len(pulse_files),\r\n        \"classification_accuracy\": 0.0,\r\n        \"prediction_accuracy\": 0.0,\r\n        \"invariants_found\": set(),\r\n        \"variants_found\": set(),\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    all_invariants = set()\r\n    all_variants = set()\r\n    \r\n    for pulse_file in pulse_files:\r\n        counts = analyze_pulse(pulse_file)\r\n        all_invariants.update([k for k in counts if counts[k] > 0])\r\n        all_variants.update([k for k in counts if counts[k] > 0])\r\n    \r\n    results[\"invariants_found\"] = len(all_invariants)\r\n    results[\"variants_found\"] = len(all_variants)\r\n    \r\n    # Classification: invariant ratio\r\n    total = results[\"invariants_found\"] + results[\"variants_found\"]\r\n    if total > 0:\r\n        results[\"classification_accuracy\"] = results[\"invariants_found\"] / total\r\n    \r\n    # Prediction: would invariants persist?\r\n    results[\"prediction_accuracy\"] = 0.75  # Placeholder - needs real prediction test\r\n    \r\n    return results\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    print(\"TIC Classifier v0.1\")\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:38:34"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1068,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 043804\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action identified: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the TIC experiment. Let me think about what this entails:\r\n\r\n1. Read the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md doc to understand the approach\r\n2. Create a script or method to analyze pulse logs for invariants vs variants\r\n3. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at the most recent pulse log to understand the format, and then create the TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- logs/pulse_2026-03-24 043705.md (most recent)\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC implementation that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that repeat across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Tests prediction ability\r\n\r\nLet me craft a concrete action - I'll create a TIC classifier script that starts analyzing the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight unifies Phase 1 and Phase 2 into one problem. The next concrete step is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier to test the hypothesis on actual pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and measure classification accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Compression = Causal Discovery\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"Phase \\d+\",\r\n    r\"research/\",\r\n    r\"\\.md\",\r\n    r\"^[A-Z].*COMPLETE.*$\",\r\n    r\"^\\[.*\\].*$\",  # Checklist items\r\n    r\"^##.*$\",      # Headers\r\n    r\"^###.*$\",     # Subheaders\r\n]\r\n\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # Dates\r\n    r\"\\d{6}\\.md\",          # Pulse timestamps\r\n    r\"\\d+s\",               # Durations\r\n    r\"^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2} \\d{6}$\",  # Session headers\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(pulse_file: Path) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    # Split by headers and key markers\r\n    blocks = re.split(r'\\n(?=##)', content)\r\n    return [b.strip() for b in blocks if b.strip()]\r\n\r\ndef classify_token(token: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a token as INVARIANT or VARIANT.\"\"\"\r\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, token):\r\n            return \"VARIANT\"\r\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, token):\r\n            return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    return \"UNKNOWN\"\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulse(pulse_file: Path) -> Dict[str, int]:\r\n    \"\"\"Count invariant vs variant tokens in a pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', content)\r\n    counts = {\"INVARIANT\": 0, \"VARIANT\": 0, \"UNKNOWN\": 0}\r\n    for token in tokens:\r\n        classification = classify_token(token)\r\n        counts[classification] += 1\r\n    return counts\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants: set, pulse_n: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict content of next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    # Simple baseline: repeat invariant structure\r\n    return f\"pulse_n+1 inherits {len(invariants)} invariant patterns\"\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment() -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    results = {\r\n        \"total_pulses\": len(pulse_files),\r\n        \"classification_accuracy\": 0.0,\r\n        \"prediction_accuracy\": 0.0,\r\n        \"invariants_found\": set(),\r\n        \"variants_found\": set(),\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    all_invariants = set()\r\n    all_variants = set()\r\n    \r\n    for pulse_file in pulse_files:\r\n        counts = analyze_pulse(pulse_file)\r\n        all_invariants.update([k for k in counts if counts[k] > 0])\r\n        all_variants.update([k for k in counts if counts[k] > 0])\r\n    \r\n    results[\"invariants_found\"] = len(all_invariants)\r\n    results[\"variants_found\"] = len(all_variants)\r\n    \r\n    # Classification: invariant ratio\r\n    total = results[\"invariants_found\"] + results[\"variants_found\"]\r\n    if total > 0:\r\n        results[\"classification_accuracy\"] = results[\"invariants_found\"] / total\r\n    \r\n    # Prediction: would invariants persist?\r\n    results[\"prediction_accuracy\"] = 0.75  # Placeholder - needs real prediction test\r\n    \r\n    return results\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    print(\"TIC Classifier v0.1\")\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:38:34","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774341544393}}
